bout%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20new%20coronavirus%20emerging%20in%20the%20future.%20She%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20global%20readiness%20to%20combat%20outbreaks%2C%20drawing%20from%20the%20lessons%20of%20the%20ongoing%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It's%20not%20just%20you.%20LinkedIn%20has%20gotten%20really%20weird.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20variety%20of%20LinkedIn%20case%20studies.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650dd5cbe453d50019f7debe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIs%20aggressively%20posting%20on%20LinkedIn%20actually%20good%20for%20your%20career%3F%20That%20may%20depend%20on%20your%20prospective%20employer's%20LinkedIn%20persona.%3Cp%3EXavier%20Lalanne-Tauzia%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20hard%20day%20for%20Matthew%20Sciannella%3A%20He%20was%20officially%20getting%20divorced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2012%20years%20of%20marriage%20and%20multiple%20children%2C%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20drifted%20apart%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20In%20early%202021%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20call%20it%20quits.%20As%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC-area%20marketing%20executive%20grappled%20with%20the%20realities%20of%20being%20suddenly%20single%20again%2C%20he%20told%20his%20friends%2C%20he%20journaled%20about%20it%2C%20and%20he%20told%20his%20family.%20And%20then%20he%20told%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20getting%20a%20divorce.%20God%20it%20sucks%20to%20write%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Sciannella%20shared%20with%20his%20several%20thousand%20professional%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D4a16b6dbc934512eab24bea8afb2c268284745010b9dcc5739e57a3d632b853d%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fmatthewsciannella_heres-my-most-human-post-ive-ever-thrown-activity-6769604891728990209-lMFg%252F%253Ftrk%253Dpublic_profile_like_view%2526originalSubdomain%253Dmt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhy%20he'd%20decided%20to%20publicize%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20news%20on%20the%20work-focused%20social%20network.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20human%20network%20for%20me%20now.%20A%20place%20where%20I%20feel%20most%20myself.%20Most%20at%20home.%20And%20most%20among%20my%20peers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20build%20our%20professional%20castles%20here%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20but%20real%20life%20shit%20happens%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20remote%20work%20across%20the%20world%20had%20blurred%20the%20lines%20between%20work%20and%20life.%20Sciannella's%20post%20touched%20a%20nerve.%20It%20accrued%20thousands%20of%20reactions%20and%20hundreds%20of%20comments.%20%26quot%3BLet%20it%20out%20brother%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20growth%20advisor%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BFuck%20the%20ROI%20conversations%20right%20now%20and%20focus%20on%20your%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20backlash%20began.%20Other%20commenters%20started%20criticizing%20his%20decision%20to%20share%20so%20openly%20with%20his%20colleagues%2C%20clients%2C%20and%20potential%20future%20employers.%20And%20a%20meme%20account%20on%20Instagram%2C%20%40BestOfLinkedIn%2C%20screenshotted%20and%20mocked%20his%20post%20to%20its%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20followers.%C2%A0It%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20this%20wouldn't%20have%20happened%20if%20you%20didn't%20share%20every%20detail%20of%20your%20personal%20life%20on%20a%20professional%20networking%20platform%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20start%20of%20a%20madcap%20workplace%20drama%20that%20laid%20bare%20an%20awkward%20truth%3A%20No%20one%20really%20knows%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bprofessional%26quot%3B%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20950%20million%20members%20as%20of%20July%2C%20LinkedIn%20is%20poised%20to%20soon%20have%20a%20billion%20users%2C%20joining%20a%20rarefied%20three-comma%20club%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20TikTok.%20Started%20in%202003%20as%20little%20more%20than%20an%20online%20repository%20for%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20the%20Microsoft-owned%20behemoth%20has%20recently%20transformed.%20Not%20only%20are%20there%20more%20users%20to%20post%2C%20but%20they're%20posting%20much%20more%20often.%20The%20number%20of%20LinkedIn%20posts%20grew%2041%25%20from%202021%20to%202023.%20But%20it's%20the%20content%20of%20the%20posts%20that's%20shifted%20the%20most%2C%20turning%20LinkedIn%20into%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20strangest%20social%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20one%20post%20from%20Peter%20Rota%2C%20an%20SEO%20specialist%20from%20Massachusetts.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20secret%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D9a5aa4fbe46d9a31c21b5907fc90f6d827125bac750724ccc06f68403ff93dec%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fpeterrota_mindset-mindsetiseverything-activity-6968896444007137281-RPMS%252F%253Futm_source%253Dshare%2526utm_medium%253Dmember_desktop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20to%20his%20thousands%20of%20followers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%202022.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20are%20not%20even%20aware%20this%20is%20a%20real%20thing.%20Since%202015%2C%20I%20have%20struggled%20with%20peeing%20in%20public%20restrooms.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERota%20went%20on%20to%20explain%20that%20his%20social-anxiety%20condition%2C%20also%20known%20as%20shy-bladder%20syndrome%2C%20had%20caused%20years%20of%20discomfort%2C%20and%20even%20provoked%20him%20to%20miss%20friends'%20weddings.%20He%20had%20a%20blowout%20trip%20planned%20to%20tour%20Europe%20with%20friends%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20and%20was%20seriously%20considering%20not%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20post%20it%3F%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20basically%20seen%20other%20people%2C%20I%20guess%2C%20share%20more%20vulnerable%20things%2C%20so%20to%20speak%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20feel%20like%20it's%20kind%20of%20just%20something%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20share%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20Over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20he'd%20seen%20and%20taken%20part%20in%20a%20pivot%20toward%20personal%20sharing%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20and%20saw%20posting%20about%20his%20condition%20as%20a%20way%20to%20both%20confront%20his%20demons%20and%20help%20with%20the%20condition%20for%20others.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20sometimes%20it%20just%20helps%20other%20people%20to%20know%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20do%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20sharing%20on%20LinkedIn%20is%20booming%2C%20people%20who%20use%20the%20platform%20say%2C%20because%20of%20tidal%20shifts%20in%20both%20social%20norms%20and%20the%20social-media%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20broad%20cultural%20attitudes%20toward%20the%20workplace%2C%20as%20well%20as%20what's%20appropriate%20to%20share%2C%20are%20evolving.%20This%20is%20partly%20driven%20by%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic%3A%20People%20were%20suddenly%20given%20free%20rein%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F09%2F16%2Fbusiness%2Flinkedin-overshare.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evulnerable%20and%20express%20their%20fears%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20front%20of%20their%20colleagues%2C%20while%20remote%20work%20simultaneously%20lowered%20inhibitions%20and%20eroded%20much%20of%20in-office%20etiquette.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20fishing%20for%20likes%20on%20LinkedIn.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650dd74ee453d50019f7df77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EXavier%20Lalanne-Tauzia%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20generational%20shift%2C%20with%20some%20younger%20people%20having%20fewer%20hang-ups%20sharing%20with%20their%20colleagues.%20Oversharing%20comes%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20much%20down%20to%20Gen%20Z%2C%20to%20be%20honest%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Catalina%20Valentino%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20entrepreneur.%20She%20found%20some%20notoriety%20from%20Davos%20earlier%20this%20year%20when%20she%20posted%20on%20LinkedIn%20about%20taking%20off%20her%20%26quot%3Bswanky%20new%20pair%20of%20Louboutins%26quot%3B%20to%20walk%20nearly%20a%20mile%20barefoot%20in%20the%20snow%20to%20a%20meeting%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20after%20her%20car%20got%20stuck.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20shocked%2C%20but%20to%20me%20it%20seemed%20normal%20to%20stop%20at%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20exactly%20the%20mindset%20of%20an%20entrepreneur.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20was%20also%2C%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20virgin%20territory%20for%20posters.%20As%20the%20platform%20built%20out%20its%20sharing%20functionality%2C%20it%20had%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20users%20but%20without%20the%20same%20culture%20of%20posting%20as%20Twitter%20or%20Instagram.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20very%20untapped%2C%26quot%3B%20Rota%20says.%20Some%20users%20found%20that%20the%20same%20post%20would%20receive%20far%20more%20engagement%20on%20LinkedIn%20as%20compared%20with%20rival%20social%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0making%20it%20an%20attractive%20place%20to%20concentrate%20their%20energies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20it's%20becoming%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town.%20Facebook%20has%20been%20a%20wasteland%20for%20years.%20X%2C%20as%20Twitter%20is%20now%20known%2C%20is%20subject%20to%20Elon%20Musk's%20mercurial%20whims.%20TikTok's%20short-form%20video%20is%20a%20different%20form%20of%20content.%20Users%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%5C%22%3Estopped%20posting%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20most%20other%20platforms.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-22%2Finstagram-twitter-and-tiktok-upheavals-are-helping-linkedin%3Fembedded-checkout%3Dtrue%26sref%3DBWbpWjRm%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAs%20Sarah%20Frier%20wrote%20in%20a%20Bloomberg%20column%20in%20August%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BLinkedIn%20is%20becoming%20a%20site%20where%20regular%20people%20actually%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20and%20post%20their%20thoughts.%20It%20might%20even%20be%20cool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20John%20Hickey%20was%20working%20in%20tech%20sales%20and%20sick%20of%20the%20culture%20of%20endless%20self-promotion.%20He%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20writer%2C%20but%20his%20days%20were%20filled%20with%20self-aggrandizing%20emails.%20So%20he%20decided%20to%20have%20some%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20millennial%20in%20San%20Francisco%20started%20posting%20the%20worst-offending%20%26quot%3BLinkedInfluencers%26quot%3B%20he%20found%20to%20his%20personal%20Twitter%20page%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20the%20shameless%20humblebrags%2C%20the%20personal%20anecdotes%20of%20dubious%20veracity%2C%20the%20%23HustleCulture%20koans%20promoting%20a%20questionable%20approach%20to%20work-life%20balance.%20They%20were%20an%20instant%20hit%2C%20and%20the%20retweets%20rolled%20in.%20So%20he%20decided%20to%20spin%20up%20a%20dedicated%20meme%20page%20poking%20fun%20at%20the%20excesses%20of%20online%20professional%20culture%20and%20the%20Ted%20Talkification%20of%20LinkedIn.%20He%20called%20it%20%40BestOfLinkedIn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20worked%20for%20me%2C%20and%20you%20represented%20my%20brand%20this%20way%2C%20you'd%20be%20terminated%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20quickly%20racked%20up%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20followers%20on%20Twitter%20and%20Instagram%2C%20and%20people%20started%20sending%20Hickey%20examples%20they%20found%20from%20their%20own%20networks.%20He%20had%20inadvertently%20transformed%20into%20a%20warrior%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20of%20the%20internet's%20weirdest%2C%20lowest-stakes%20culture%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20post%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FChFW-CPLKbl%2F%3Fimg_index%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20skewered%20a%20CEO%20who%20talked%20about%20being%20%26quot%3Bvulnerable%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20shared%20a%20crying%20selfie%20after%20laying%20off%20employees.%20In%20another%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCnzcBRiLyx9%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriticized%20a%20user%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20wrote%20about%20taking%20time%20off%20after%20her%20father%20died%20but%20made%20sure%20to%20keep%20checking%20LinkedIn.%20(He%20also%20leaked%20Peter%20Rota's%20bashful%20urinary%20tract.)%20A%20larger%20rival%20account%20emerged%2C%20State%20Of%20LinkedIn%2C%20and%20a%20Reddit%20community%20thrived%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FLinkedInLunatics%2Ftop%2F%3Ft%3Dyear%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BLinkedIn%20Lunatics%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Hickey%20came%20across%20Sciannella's%20post%20about%20his%20divorce%2C%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20perfect%20example%20of%20online%20oversharing.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20my%20God%20%E2%80%94%20he%20really%20just%20put%20that%20all%20out%20there%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled%20thinking.%20He%20redacted%20Sciannella's%20name%2C%20as%20he%20always%20did%20for%20the%20posts%20he%20featured%2C%20but%20it%20made%20it%20back%20to%20Sciannella%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHickey%20wasn't%20ready%20for%20what%20happened%20next.%20A%20couple%20of%20days%20after%20he%20posted%2C%20an%20angry%20email%20landed%20in%20his%20inbox%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Sciannella's%20boss.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20realize%20how%20dangerous%20it%20is%20to%20troll%20via%20LinkedIn%20posts%3F%20In%20two%20seconds%2C%20I%20found%20who%20you%20work%20for%2C%20who%20the%20partners%20of%20your%20agency%20are%2C%20who%20your%20clients%20are%2C%20etc.%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned%20ominously.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20worked%20for%20me%2C%20and%20you%20represented%20my%20brand%20this%20way%2C%20you'd%20be%20terminated%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20Hickey%20received%20from%20Sciannella%20was%20even%20more%20blunt.%20It%20sent%20him%20an%20address%20and%20challenged%20him%20to%20repeat%20what%20he%20had%20written%20to%20his%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20surest%20sign%20of%20LinkedIn's%20hotness%2C%20its%20posts%20are%20now%20the%20subject%20of%20scathing%20satires.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJack%20Raines%2C%20an%20MBA%20student%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20has%20perfected%20the%20art%20of%20LinkedIn%20parodies.%20After%20New%20York%20announced%20a%20%24100%20incentive%20to%20encourage%20residents%20to%20get%20vaccinated%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opindia.com%2F2022%2F10%2Flinkedin-user-claims-he-made-100000-by-getting-1000-covid-shots-attention-seeking-shtposting-social-media%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20posted%20that%20he'd%20earned%20%24100%2C000%20by%20getting%201%2C000%20jabs%20in%2016%20days%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BOpportunities%20like%20these%20are%20rare%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20capitalize%20on%20them%20if%20you%20want%20to%20successfully%20build%20wealth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20sagely%20advised%20his%20followers.%20Some%20of%20them%20inevitably%20fall%20for%20his%20shtick%20and%20believe%20they're%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Cohen%2C%20a%20healthtech%20executive%20in%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%2C%20is%20another%20prolific%20LinkedIn%20shitposter%2C%20whose%20best%20work%20includes%20an%20infamous%20lifehack%20post%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fanothercohen%2Fstatus%2F1565167463268065281%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecooking%20butter-garlic%20chicken%20in%20a%20hotel%20coffee%20machine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(%26quot%3BAlthough%20my%20company%20allows%20me%20to%20expense%20dinner%20while%20traveling%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20save%20money%20because%20I%20know%20that%20every%20dollar%20counts%20on%20the%20P%26amp%3BL%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20cooks%20butter-garlic%20chicken%20in%20a%20hotel%20coffee%20machine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650dd96023ce9d001908974a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EXavier%20Lalanne-Tauzia%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3ECohen's%20and%20Raines'%20posts%20now%20sometimes%20play%20off%20each%20other%2C%20creating%20a%20kind%20of%20LinkedIn%20Cinematic%20Universe%20of%20connected%20stories.%20This%20summer%2C%20Raines%20posted%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20personal%20finance%20tip%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D39ac55d5156718af29d18f9d81cc5db57a14d8736c5bb6a8122da88e67b28bd6%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fjackraines_wealthhack-worksmarternotharder-airb2c-activity-7092557818217541633-_vMP%252F%253Futm_source%253Dshare%2526utm_medium%253Dmember_desktop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esell%20off%20the%20furniture%20of%20the%20Airbnbs%20you%20stay%20in%20on%20vacation%20for%20free%20money!%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0prompting%20Cohen%20to%20post%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D3e9b5d3d24a20085df7347b64d8195a6f6809058d35ec40906f1d9b56ac0ff36%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Falexander-cohen_airbnb-nightmare-activity-7092574417171427328-t1pj%252F%253Futm_source%253Dshare%2526utm_medium%253Dmember_desktop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20tongue-in-cheek%20PSA%20for%20Airbnb%20entrepreneurs%20about%20the%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20suspected%20culprit%20%E2%80%94%20a%20woman%20named%20Jacqueline%20Rainey%20%E2%80%94%20has%20secured%20bookings%20at%20my%20other%20four%20properties%20for%20the%20next%20three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20lamented.%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20irony%20of%20Raines%20is%20that%20despite%20his%20insincerity%2C%20he's%20just%20as%20relentlessly%20self-promotional%20as%20the%20LinkedIn%20users%20he%20mocks.%20He%20consistently%20hawks%20the%20newsletter%20he%20works%20for%2C%20Young%20Money%2C%20and%20has%20started%20running%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D8f693dd58236248fea6594e119200192750a0d1212701d6663f30faacc394c1d%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fjackraines_creatine-wanderinginthewoodslikeanolddog-activity-7093293769659142148-dDXb%253Futm_source%253Dshare%2526utm_medium%253Dmember_desktop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esponsored%20posts%20for%20health%20supplements%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20intends%20to%20parlay%20the%20audience%20he's%20built%20into%20a%20content-related%20finance%20job%20once%20he%20finishes%20his%20MBA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20it%20is%20being%20funny%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20and%2C%20yeah%2C%20it's%20the%20same%20thing%20as%20somebody%20building%20a%20YouTube%20channel%3A%20They're%20trying%20to%20get%20engagement%2C%20but%20if%20their%20content's%20good%2C%20is%20it%20really%20engagement-bait%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo.%20The%20ones%20that%20I%20don't%20like%20are%20people%20trying%20to%20act%20like%20they're%20some%20finance%20guru%20%E2%80%94%20'Here's%20how%20you%20get%20rich%2C%20escape%20the%209-to-5'%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20sell%20you%20some%20pyramid%20scheme-leadership%20course.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20faced%20blowback%20for%20his%20posting.%20In%20the%20fall%20of%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJack_Raines%2Fstatus%2F1584317256766722050%2Fphoto%2F1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20wrote%20a%20satirical%20post%20about%20how%20he'd%20found%20a%20way%20to%20avoid%20paying%20for%20food%20in%20New%20York%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20wandering%20into%20hotel%20restaurants%20and%20charging%20the%20meal%20to%20a%20random%20room.%20%26quot%3BFollow%20me%20for%20more%20personal%20finance%20tips%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20signed%20off%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%2C%20he%20found%20himself%20abruptly%20called%20into%20the%20Columbia%20dean%20of%20students'%20office.%20An%20outraged%20alum%20had%20complained%20about%20what%20they%20thought%20was%20a%20sincere%20admission%20of%20theft%20by%20a%20student%20and%20wanted%20him%20punished.%20Thus%20proceeded%20a%20surreal%20conversation%20in%20which%20he%20explained%20to%20the%20dean%20the%20ironic%20bent%20of%20his%20LinkedIn%20persona%20and%20that%2C%20no%2C%20he%20wasn't%20really%20stealing%20food%20from%20hotels%20around%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20ultimately%20thought%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bfunny%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20(The%20dean%20declined%20to%20comment.)%20And%20he%20doesn't%20regret%20the%20post%3A%20The%20meeting%20with%20the%20dean%20was%20a%20good%20networking%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20aggressively%20posting%20on%20LinkedIn%20actually%20good%20for%20your%20career%3F%20That%20may%20depend%20on%20your%20prospective%20employer's%20LinkedIn%20persona.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Reid%20is%20skeptical%20of%20LinkedIn%20self-aggrandizement.%20A%20creative%20director%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20he's%20hired%2C%20fired%2C%20and%20managed%20throughout%20his%20career%20%E2%80%94%20and%20views%20a%20lot%20of%20nominally%20self-promotional%20posts%20as%20potentially%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20oversharing%20in%20general%20is%20definitely%20at%20least%20a%20pink%20flag%2C%20probably%20a%20red%20flag%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20shows%2C%20to%20me%2C%20misunderstanding%20how%20that%20platform%20in%20particular%2C%20in%20social%20media%20in%20general%20work%2C%20and%20it%20just%20shows%20bad%20judgment.%20So%20I%20think%20looking%20out%20at%20people's%20social%20footprint%20or%20hiring%2C%20is%20there%20evidence%20of%20spectacularly%20bad%20judgment%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20feelings%20on%20the%20subject%20were%20perhaps%20hardened%20by%20an%20unusual%20phone%20call%20to%20his%20employer%2C%20an%20Oakland%20marketing%20firm%2C%20in%20early%202021.%20At%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20line%20was%20a%20man%20named%20Jon%20Franko%2C%20and%20he%20was%20furious%20about%20one%20of%20Reid's%20subordinates%3A%20John%20Hickey.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20Reid's%20boss%2C%20the%20outraged%20Franko%20asked%20whether%20the%20company%20knew%20that%20Hickey%20operated%20a%20pseudonymous%20meme%20account%20on%20Twitter%20and%20Instagram%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20%40BestofLinkedIn%20had%20just%20mocked%20an%20employee%20at%20Franko's%20marketing%20firm%3A%20Matthew%20Sciannella%2C%20the%20divorc%C3%A9.%20Franko%20wanted%20to%20see%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20short%20and%20surreal%20conversation%2C%20Reid%20and%20his%20boss%20spoke%20with%20Hickey.%20Hickey%20had%20already%20deleted%20the%20post%2C%20as%20he%20does%20when%20he%20gets%20blowback.%20Reid%20viewed%20Franko's%20call%20as%20an%20implicit%20demand%20for%20Hickey%20to%20be%20fired%2C%20but%20that%20was%20never%20going%20to%20happen%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20because%20he%20had%20actually%20taken%20a%20chance%20and%20first%20hired%20Hickey%20for%20his%20copywriting%20job%20off%20the%20strength%20off%20the%20meme%20account.%20%26quot%3BHe%20obviously%20understood%20how%20to%20mold%20culture%20through%20media%20and%20social%20media%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Reid%20had%20thought.%20(Franko%20said%20he%20would%20not%20have%20asked%20for%20Hickey%20to%20be%20fired%2C%20though%20he%20may%20have%20called%20for%20a%20disciplinary%20conversation.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESciannella%20was%20acting%20hypocritically%2C%20Reid%20believed%3A%20He%20was%20willing%20to%20put%20himself%20out%20there%20with%20highly%20personal%20posts%20but%20couldn't%20take%20the%20heat%20that%20came%20with%20being%20in%20the%20public%20eye.%20%26quot%3BJump%20in%20the%20snake%20pit%2C%20and%20you%20get%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranko%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20thought%20that%20the%20%40BestOfLinkedIn%20post%20was%20an%20unfair%20and%20wildly%20unprofessional%20jab%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20he%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20have%20his%20employees'%20backs.%20%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20that%20use%20LinkedIn%20in%20a%20really%20bad%20way%20that's%20super%20annoying%20and%20is%20a%20major%20turnoff%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3B'I%20saw%20a%20starving%20dog%20today%20and%20I%20saved%20it%2C%20and%20then%20it%20made%20me%20think%20about%20business.'%20That%20shit's%20annoying%2C%20and%20I%20get%20it.%20I%20didn't%20see%20Matt's%20posts%20like%20that%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%2C%20their%20LinkedIn%20posts%20don't%20escalate%20so%20rapidly.%20According%20to%20Joseph%20Yeh%2C%20a%20tech%20recruiter%20in%20California%20who%20used%20to%20work%20for%20LinkedIn%2C%20revelatory%20posting%20is%20a%20balancing%20act.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20is%20important%20to%20engage%2C%20and%20at%20least%20be%20relevant%20and%20know%20that%20you%20are%20checking%20in%20and%20that%20you're%20commenting%20and%20it's%20a%20quote-unquote%20a%20'live%20profile%2C'%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20for%2C%20A%2C%20for%20people%20to%20remember%20who%20you%20are.%20Two%2C%20it%20also%20helps%20for%20you%20to%20understand%20what%20the%20ecosystem%20is%20looking%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flipside%2C%20the%20wrong%20content%20can%20be%20off-putting%3A%20%26quot%3BOn%20LinkedIn%20people%20will%20still%20be%20looking%20at%20it%20going%3A%20This%20is%20how%20I%20want%20to%20present%20myself%20as%20a%20professional%20to%20the%20outside%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man's%20suit%20gets%20bigger%20and%20bigger.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650dd9e223ce9d00190897a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EXavier%20Lalanne-Tauzia%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EExactly%20what%20is%20and%20isn't%20acceptable%20on%20LinkedIn%20depends%20on%20the%20norms%20of%20your%20industry%3B%20tech%20sales%20representatives%20may%20have%20very%20different%20ideas%20of%20professionalism%20compared%20with%20arbitration%20lawyers.%20Played%20right%2C%20it%20can%20help%20you%20stand%20out%20and%20get%20ahead%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20you%20don't%20push%20it%20too%20far.%20And%20opting%20out%20of%20the%20rat%20race%20entirely%20by%20not%20having%20a%20LinkedIn%20account%20may%20also%20be%20viewed%20as%20a%20red%20flag%2C%20Yeh%20warned.%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20does%20not%20want%20to%20be%20a%20place%20where%20posts%20go%20viral.%20That's%20the%20message%20from%20Daniel%20Roth%2C%20the%20site's%20editor%20in%20chief%20who%20has%20been%20with%20the%20company%20since%202011%2C%20after%20a%20previous%20stint%20as%20Fortune%20magazine's%20managing%20editor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%20or%20so%2C%20the%20site's%20algorithm%20has%20been%20tweaked%20to%20prioritize%20what%20Roth%20calls%20%26quot%3Bknowledge%26quot%3B%20content%20%E2%80%94%20posts%20that%20will%20actually%20help%20people%20get%20ahead%20in%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20self-promotional%20diatribes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20COVID-propelled%20boom%20in%20personal%20sharing%2C%20Roth%20says%2C%20the%20pendulum%20has%20swung%20back%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20all%20the%20way%20back%20to%20how%20things%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BThe%20new%20normal%20is%20that%20you%20do%20talk%20in%20the%20office%2C%20you%20are%20more%20willing%20to%20show%20who%20you%20are%20as%20a%20person%20as%20well%20as%20how%20you%20operate%20as%20a%20professional%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20kind%20of%20vulnerability%20I%20think%20is%20a%20permanent%20part%20of%20how%20people%20are%20posting%20on%20LinkedIn.%20So%20it's%20knowledge%20first%2C%20but%20it's%20knowledge%20plus%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHickey%20and%20Sciannella's%20imbroglio%20may%20be%20telling%20of%20which%20way%20the%20wind%20is%20blowing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESciannella%20didn't%20actually%20know%20his%20boss%20Franko%20had%20called%20Hickey's%20employer%20until%20days%20after%20the%20fact.%C2%A0He%20had%20just%20flagged%20the%20%40BestOfLinkedIn%20post%20in%20a%20company%20Slack%20channel%2C%20and%20Franko%20decided%20to%20take%20matters%20into%20his%20own%20hands.%20Nothing%20more%20came%20of%20Franko's%20demands%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D83aecdd876a9e0a802b0045db665c02b1c3ca636d66b6e15da563dd5c87b92df%26postID%3D64ff281f909a7a425c60a426%26postSlug%3Dhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fjonfranko_being-a-troll-on-the-internet-is-just-an-activity-6771265231512506368-UCN-%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20he%20subsequently%20wrote%20about%20the%20episode%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20simply%20hope%20this%20is%20a%20reminder%20for%20all%20of%20us%20to%20play%20nice%20on%20LinkedIn.%20Because%20if%20we%20don't%2C%20we%20can%20be%20seconds%20away%20from%20the%20unemployment%20line%20and%20burning%20all%20of%20the%20bridges%20we've%20worked%20so%20hard%20to%20build.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHickey%20and%20Sciannella%20did%20not%2C%20ultimately%2C%20fight.%20Instead%2C%20Hickey%20kept%20working%20at%20the%20firm%20for%20roughly%20another%20year%20before%20becoming%20an%20associate%20creative%20director%2C%20working%20with%20top-tier%20clients%20including%20Salesforce%2C%20Jameson%2C%20and%20the%20New%20York%20Mets.%20Two%20years%20on%2C%20he%20rarely%20checks%20LinkedIn%2C%20now%20posting%20to%20his%20meme%20account%20only%20about%20once%20a%20month%2C%20down%20from%20his%20daily%20peak%20a%20year%20or%20so%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20lightning-rod%20moments%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20well%2C%20I%20can't%20not%20say%20something%20about%20these%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20kind%20of%20going%20through%20the%20daily%20%E2%80%94%20'Let's%20make%20fun%20of%20this%20stay-at-home-mom%20who's%20putting%20up%20on%20LinkedIn%20that%20her%206-year-old%20told%20her%20that%20she's%20Superwoman'%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20feels%20like%20I'm%20punching%20down%20a%20little%20bit%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESciannella%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20in%20a%20good%20place.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%2C%20very%20angry%20at%20that%20moment.%20It%20was%20obviously%20a%20very%20turbulent%20time%20in%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20peace%20of%20mind%20about%20it.%20And%20I%20think%20foundationally%2C%20I'm%20a%20lot%20more%20happy.%26quot%3B%20He's%20had%20a%20few%20promotions%20and%20job%20changes.%20And%20he's%20still%20active%20on%20the%20social%20network%2C%20where%20he%20now%20has%20about%206%2C000%20followers%2C%20sharing%20updates%20on%20his%20work%20and%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%202023%2C%20he%20remarried.%20He%20posted%20about%20it%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Frob-price%5C%22%3ERob%20Price%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20for%20Insider%20and%20writes%20features%20and%20investigations%20about%20the%20technology%20industry.%20His%20Signal%20number%20is%20%2B1%20650-636-6268%2C%20and%20his%20email%20is%20rprice%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695634201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650dddbae453d50019f7e1db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Divorce%2C%20trouble%20peeing%2C%20and%20stealing%20hotel%20food%3A%20Why%20did%20a%20job%20network%20become%20everyone's%20favorite%20place%20for%20oversharing%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rprice%40insider.com%20(Rob%20Price)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Asiad%20Final%20Live%3A%20India%20Beat