t%20attend%20due%20to%20work%20and%20that%20both%20families%20focused%20on%20blessings%20rather%20than%20gifts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpriyanka-chopra-gives-newlyweds-parineeti-chopra-and-raghav-chadha-marriage-tips-protect-this-beautiful-love%2Farticleshow%2F103928338.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20states%205%20days%20before%20we%20got%20the%20return-to-office%20order%20at%20Amazon%2C%20so%20I%20quit.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20we'd%20be%20forced%20back%20into%20the%20office.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b16b81f9a259001947598c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222917%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGabe%20Ginsberg%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESophia%20Carter%20was%20working%20as%20a%20talent-management%20specialist%20at%20Amazon%20in%20Chicago.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20relocated%20to%20Raleigh%2C%20NC%2C%20five%20days%20before%20Amazon%20announced%20its%20return-to-office%20order.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECarter%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20move%20again%2C%20so%20she%20quit%20her%20job%20at%20Amazon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Sophia%20Carter%2C%20an%20ex-Amazon%20employee.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability%2C%20I%20started%20working%20remotely%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20after%20years%20of%20stressful%20in-office%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sophia%20Carter%2C%20ex-Amazon%20employee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650d7cb619f33e0019046d19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESophie%20Carter%20has%20a%20stress%20tolerance%20disability%20that%20prevents%20her%20from%20working%20in-office%3Cp%3ESophia%20Carter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20working%20remotely%20since%20October%202019%20and%20took%20a%20sabbatical%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20job%20as%20an%20Amazon%20talent-management%20specialist%20in%20September%202022.%20When%20I%20was%20hired%2C%20Amazon%20office%20employees%20were%20working%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20team's%20senior%20leadership%20had%20to%20fly%20to%20different%20cities%20for%20in-person%20strategic%20meetings%20with%20other%20senior%20leaders%2C%20but%20no%20one%20else%20was%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20into%20the%20Chicago%20office%20voluntarily%20for%20meetings%20and%20team%20bonding%20once%20a%20month%20over%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBeing%20in%20an%20office%20environment%20makes%20my%20disability%20worse%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20stress-intolerance%20disorder%20and%20work%20is%20inherently%20stressful.%20My%20stressors%20make%20me%20both%20physically%20and%20mentally%20sick.%20An%20in-person%20office%20environment%20exacerbates%20my%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20to%20be%20hospitalized%20multiple%20times%20for%20stress-related%20illnesses%20after%20working%20in%20person%20for%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20of%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20from%20home%20allows%20me%20to%20control%20my%20environment%20and%20minimize%20stressors.%20I%20can%20take%20breaks%20and%20reduce%20the%20impact%20of%20stress%20on%20my%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20also%20be%20my%20authentic%20self%20while%20working%20without%20masking%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20which%20takes%20a%20huge%20mental%20and%20physical%20load%20off%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20to%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20there%20were%20no%20rumblings%20of%20RTO%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20tired%20of%20the%20long%2C%20dark%2C%20cold%20winters%20in%20Chicago.%20I%20wanted%20a%20metropolitan%20location%20that%20was%20warmer%2C%20safe%2C%20and%20not%20too%20big.%20Raleigh%20checked%20all%20my%20boxes.%20People%20here%20are%20friendly%20and%20welcoming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20Amazon's%20internal%20messaging%20was%20that%20we%20would%20be%20remote%20indefinitely%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0there%20were%20no%20whispers%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-return-to-office-policy-news-updates-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERTO%20was%20coming%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20confident%20relocating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20mention%20my%20move%20to%20my%20manager%20because%20I%20never%20felt%20like%20there%20would%20be%20any%20threat%20of%20me%20having%20to%20go%20into%20the%20office%20anytime%20soon%2C%20if%20ever.%20Members%20of%20my%20team%20lived%20in%20different%20places%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20less%20than%20a%20week%20after%20I%20moved%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-voluntary-resignation-employees-relocate-rto-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%20issued%20its%20RTO%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20order.%20Employees%20had%20to%20be%20working%20in%20the%20office%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%20three%20days%20a%20week%20from%20May%201.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20whole%20team%20wanted%20to%20keep%20working%20remotely%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20team's%20leadership%20advocated%20for%20our%20team%20to%20remain%20remote%20since%20we%20were%20spread%20across%20the%20country.%20Even%20if%20we%20all%20went%20to%20our%20nearest%20offices%2C%20we%20still%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20collaborate%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20work%20involved%20sensitive%20employee%20data%2C%20so%20we%20couldn't%20have%20meetings%20or%20calls%20in%20a%20cubicle%20or%20open-office%20floor%20plan.%20We'd%20always%20need%20the%20security%20and%20privacy%20of%20a%20private%20room%2C%20so%20there%20was%20another%20wrench%20in%20the%20RTO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20confident%20that%20my%20leaders%20did%20their%20best%20to%20find%20alternatives%20and%20advocate%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20have%20as%20much%20power%20as%20the%20C-suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20knew%20I%20wasn't%20going%20back%20to%20Chicago%20or%20in-person%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20returning%20to%20Chicago%20or%20another%20Amazon%20hub%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20off%20the%20table.%20Amazon%20wasn't%20talking%20about%20relocation%20assistance%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20relocation%20was%20expensive%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20work.%20I%20love%20Raleigh%20and%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20move%20again%2C%20so%20returning%20to%20a%20hub%20was%20never%20on%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20took%20me%2090%20days%20to%20find%20a%20new%20remote%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20RTO%20message%20came%20out%2C%20I%20waited%20to%20see%20what%20my%20direct%20leadership%20chain%20would%20do.%20Over%20the%20next%20month%2C%20it%20became%20apparent%20that%20all%20of%20us%20would%20have%20to%20submit%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaired%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-layoffs-second-round-9000-job-jobs-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20mass%20layoffs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20happening%20nearly%20every%20quarter%2C%20I%20didn't%20feel%20I%20had%20job%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20applying%20for%20remote%20jobs%20in%20April%2C%20which%20made%20my%20search%20difficult%20because%20entirely%20remote%20jobs%20aren't%20as%20plentiful%20as%20they%20were%20in%202020%20and%20competition%20is%20tough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20three%20months%2C%20I%20received%20an%20offer%20from%20another%20Fortune%20100%20company%20to%20work%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELeaving%20Amazon%20was%20a%20blessing%20in%20disguise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20blessing%20in%20disguise.%20If%20Amazon%20had%20never%20announced%20RTO%20or%20layoffs%2C%20I%20would%20probably%20still%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20like%20the%20new%20job%20much%20more%20and%20it's%20a%20much%20better%20match%20for%20my%20skill%20set%20and%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20role%20at%20Amazon%20was%20very%20task-oriented.%20Get%20this%20done%2C%20get%20that%20done.%20My%20new%20role%20is%20strategic.%20I%20get%20to%20partner%20with%20senior%20business%20leaders%20and%20determine%20the%20talent%20strategy%20to%20make%20their%20business%20strategy%20a%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20request%20from%20Insider%20to%20comment%20on%20Amazon's%20return-to-office%20order%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20company%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20being%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20is%20the%20right%20long-term%20approach%20because%20it%20drives%20culture%2C%20team%20connection%2C%20innovation%2C%20and%20learning.%C2%A0We%20also%20appreciate%20that%20there%20will%20be%20exceptions%20based%20on%20an%20employee's%20individual%20circumstances.%20Insider%20wouldn't%20share%20the%20information%20necessary%20for%20us%20to%20verify%20this%20account%2C%20however%20we%20have%20processes%20in%20place%20for%20employees%20to%20request%20exceptions%20or%20accommodations%2C%20and%20if%20an%20employee%20is%20asked%20to%20relocate%2C%20we%20provide%20financial%20assistance.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-quit-return-to-office-order-amazon-rto-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695633664000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b83497a46ce30019a1d539%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co