l%20Airport%20on%20August%2010%2C%20which%20is%20located%20about%2020%20miles%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20capital%20of%20Kyiv.%3Cp%3EIgor%20Lesiv%2Faerovokzal.net%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20talks%20to%20rebuild%20the%20beloved%20An-225%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAntonovCompany%2Fstatus%2F1589730670502633474%5C%22%3EAntonov%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20in%20November%20to%20cost%20about%20%24502%20million%20%E2%80%94%20new%20photos%20taken%20by%20Ukrainian%20photographer%20and%20journalist%20Igor%20Lesiv%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faerovokzal.net%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAeroVokzal.net%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20shared%20with%20Insider%20show%20its%20dismantling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20look%20at%20what%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantonov-an-225-mriya-worlds-largest-cargo-plane-history-details-2020-4%23the-beloved-plane-adorned-in-a-yellow-and-blue-paint-job-was-a-symbol-of-pride-for-ukraine-having-been-built-by-ukrainian-aircraft-manufacturer-antonov-2%5C%22%3EAn-225%20looked%20like%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20after%20the%20attack%20at%20Hostomel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20colossal%20An-225%20was%20equipped%20with%20six%20Ukrainian-made%20Ivchenko%20Progress%20D-18T%20engines%2C%20two%20tail%20fins%20that%20towered%20six%20stories%20high%2C%20and%20a%20giant%20nose-loading%20door.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221662%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20An-225%20on%20the%20runway%20before%20its%20destruction.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650e1c6d23ce9d001908a7a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221247%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20An-225%20before%20its%20destruction.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20Agency%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Myria%20was%20based%20off%20the%20smaller%20AN-124%20Ruslan%20aircraft%2C%2055%20of%20which%20were%20b