C%20delivery%20personnel%2C%20marketing%20executives%2C%20sales%20and%20business%20development%20executives%20and%20housekeeping%20staff%20among%20others.%20These%20jobs%20are%20critical%20because%20the%20employees%20in%20these%20roles%20are%20often%20the%20face%20of%20the%20company.%20Their%20interactions%20with%20customers%20can%20significantly%20impact%20a%20company%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20and%20customer%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20comes%20after%20companies%20went%20on%20a%20hiring%20spree%20after%20in%20FY22%20when%20businesses%20reopened%20after%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EData%20also%20showed%20that%20average%20monthly%20salaries%20for%20frontline%20workers%20decreased%20by%204.5%25%20to%20Rs%2021%2C700%20in%20FY23%2C%20%3Cem%3EMSN%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msn.com%2Fen-in%2Fmoney%2Fnews%2Fnew-frontline-jobs-decline-17-5-in-fy23-study%2Far-AA1hczKF%3Focid%3Dfinance-verthp-feeds%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIFM%20%26amp%3B%20IT%20recorded%20the%20highest%20monthly%20average%20salaries%20at%20Rs%2025%2C700%20and%20salaries%20in%20this%20sector%20increased%20by%2017%25%20compared%20to%20FY22.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20BFSI%20and%20logistics%20%26amp%3B%20mobility%2C%20offering%20salaries%20of%20Rs%2022%2C000%20and%20Rs%2021%2C800%20per%20month%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20hiring%20numbers%20may%20improve%20this%20year%20as%20the%20ongoing%20festive%20season%20is%20leading%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20demand%20for%20manpower%20with%20companies%20looking%20to%20hire%20a%20combination%20of%20on-roll%2C%20on%20third-party%20roll%2C%20and%20gig%20workers%20to%20meet%20the%20rise%20in%20consumption%2C%20Pravin%20Agarwala%2C%20cofounder%20and%20group%20CEO%20of%20BetterPlace%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20in%20FY23%2C%20the%20logistics%20and%20mobility%20sector%20replaced%20e-commerce%20as%20the%20highest%20employment%20industry%20for%20frontline%20workers%20with%20total%20demand%20increasing%20by%20111%25%20during%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20sectors%20like%20retail%20and%20warehousing%2C%20companies%20are%20looking%20to%20hire%20more%20women%20gig%20workers%20as%20hiring%20women%20results%20in%20better%20efficiency.%20Attrition%20in%20men%20is%20higher%20than%20in%20women.%20Besides%2C%20companies%20are%20focusing%20on%20ESG%20(environmental%2C%20social%20and%20governance)%20goals%2C%E2%80%9D%20Agarwala%20told%C2%A0the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20expects%20variablisation%20of%20workforce%20to%20increase%20going%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20gig%20jobs%20have%20continued%20to%20grow%20stronger%2C%20(permanent)%20frontline%20jobs%20have%20not%20grown%20so%20much%E2%80%A6%20the%20end%20of%20FY22%20and%20beginning%20of%20FY23%20showed%20positive%20growth%20in%20demand%20but%20slowly%2C%20employers%20reduced%20vacancies%20due%20to%20various%20reasons%20like%20slowdown%20in%20business%2C%20business%20losses%2C%20over-hiring%2C%20cost%20of%20hiring%2C%20etc%E2%80%A6%20most%20enterprises%20are%20looking%20to%20variablise%20their%20workforce%20cost%20by%20moving%20to%20a%20gig%20model%20of%20workforce%20management%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fgig-jobs-continue-to-grow-stronger-in-tough-times%2Farticleshow%2F103914246.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695626148000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2F8391859530_aefbe96f68_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fonly-6-6-million-frontline-jobs-created-in-fy23-a-decline-of-17-5-from-fy22-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20decline%20happened%20due%20to%20cautious%20hiring%20by%20companies%20amid%20macroeconomic%