is%20estimated%20to%20hold%20at%20least%20a%20cup%20of%20rubble%20from%20an%20asteroid%20known%20as%20Bennu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20like%20%E2%80%98Wow!'%E2%80%9D%20said%20NASA%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%2C%20who%20was%20in%20Utah%20training%20for%20her%20own%20space%20capsule%20mission.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20just%20amazing.%20It%20can%20go%20from%20the%20movies%2C%20but%20this%20is%20reality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20mission%20important%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20was%20launched%20in%20September%202016%20by%20NASA%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona%20to%20gather%20samples%20from%20Bennu%2C%20an%20asteroid%20rich%20in%20carbon%20and%20classified%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnear-Earth%20object.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20capsule%20landed%20on%20Bennu%E2%80%99s%20surface%20in%202020%20and%20collected%20about%20nine%20ounces%20(250%20grams)%20of%20dust%20from%20its%20stony%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20sample%20return%20is%20really%20historic%2C%E2%80%9D%20NASA%20scientist%20Amy%20Simon%20told%20the%20AFP%20news%20agency.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20sample%20we%E2%80%99ve%20brought%20back%20since%20the%20Apollo%20moon%20rocks%E2%80%9D%20were%20returned%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20sample%20was%20taken%20to%20NASA%20laboratories%20in%20Texas%20for%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EScientists%20believe%20that%20by%20examining%20the%20samples%2C%20we%20can%20gain%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20how%20our%20solar%20system%20was%20formed%20and%20how%20Earth%20became%20habitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695620598000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25110114%2FF60380AWwAE41YU.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fosiris-rex-nasa-capsule-carrying-asteroid-samples-lands-in-us%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pebbles%20an