20the%20time%20when%20the%20assembly%20election%20results%20were%20declared%2C%2035%20women%20were%20elected%20in%202012%2C%2042%20in%202017%20and%2047%20in%202022.%20The%20others%20were%20elected%20in%20subsequent%20by-polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20out%20of%20the%20total%20134%20women%20candidates%20elected%20since%202012%2C%2046%20belonged%20to%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20category%2C%20all%20of%20them%20winning%20in%20reserved%20constituencies.%20The%20traditional%20UC%20were%20the%20second%20largest%20bloc%2C%20with%2042%20women%20MLAs%20while%20there%20were%2039%20women%20OBC%20MLAs.%20Seven%20Muslim%20women%20MLAs%20have%20also%20been%20elected%20since%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F15130615%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F15130615%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F15130615%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20we%20consider%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20women%20individuals%20elected%20as%20MLAs%20since%202012%20%E2%80%93%20107%20%E2%80%93%20there%20were%20more%20UCs%20(32)%20than%20OBCs%20(31)%2C%20showing%20the%20disproportionate%20representation%20enjoyed%20by%20the%20UCs%2C%20who%20are%20a%20minority%20within%20the%20Hindu%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%2084%20women%20MLAs%20were%20elected%20once%2C%2019%20were%20elected%20twice%20and%20four%20won%20on%20three%20occasions%20since%202012.%20Of%20the%2019%20women%20MLAs%20who%20were%20elected%20twice%2C%20there%20were%20six%20each%20from%20OBC%20and%20UC%20communities%20while%20seven%20were%20Dalits.%20Among%20the%20MLAs%20elected%20thrice%2C%20one%20was%20OBC%2C%20one%20Dalit%20and%20two%20UC%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20exclusion%20of%20a%20defined%20quota%20for%20OBC%20women%20within%20the%2033%25%20women%20reservation%20bill%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20%E2%80%93%20the%20bill%20was%20subsequently%20passed%20by%20both%20Houses%20of%20parliament%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20a%20key%20question%20raised%20by%20opposition%20parties%20led%20by%20the%20Congress.%20They%20have%20even%20demanded%20a%20similar%20quota%20for%20Muslim%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOpposition%20party%20MPs%20flagged%20concerns%20that%20without%20a%20defined%20quota%20for%20OBC%20and%20Muslim%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20State%20Assemblies%2C%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20Bill%20would%20be%20incomplete%20in%20a%20graded%2C%20caste-ridden%20society%20where%20the%20backward%20and%20marginalised%20castes%20and%20communities%2C%20in%20particular%20their%20women%2C%20were%20underrepresented%20in%20all%20spheres%20of%20life.%20The%20new%20bill%20provides%20one-third%20sub-quota%20for%20SC%20and%20ST%20women%20on%20the%20seats%20constitutionally%20already%20reserved%20for%20the%20SC%20and%20ST%20communities%2C%20and%20does%20not%20create%20a%20new%20category%20for%20OBCs%20or%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20demand%20to%20provide%20a%20defined%20quota%20for%20OBC%20women%20was%20raised%20by%20all%20major%20opposition%20parties%20in%20the%20key%20states%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar%2C%20where%20socialist%20Mandal-era%20parties%20had%20earlier%20opposed%20the%20women%20reservation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20it%20did%20not%20provide%20intersectional%20representation.%20When%20the%20Congress-led%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20was%20in%20power%2C%20top%20socialist%20leaders%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav%2C%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Sharad%20Yadav%20had%20argued%20that%20without%20defined%20quotas%20within%20the%20women%20reservation%20for%20OBCs%2C%20SCs%2C%20STs%20and%20Muslims%2C%20the%20law%20would%20primarily%20benefit%20privileged%20women%20from%20urban%20areas%20instead%20of%20empowering%20marginalised%20women%20who%20lagged%20in%20terms%20of%20literacy%2C%20cultural%20and%20social%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F15130551%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F15130551%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F15130551%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20level%2C%20too%2C%20in%20the%20last%20three%20general%20elections%20held%20in%202009%2C%202014%20and%202019%2C%20excluding%20by-polls%2C%20we%20find%20that%20UC%20women%20had%20a%20greater%20presence%20than%20OBC%20women%20as%20well%20as%20Dalit%20women.%20In%202009%2C%2011%20women%20MPs%20were%20elected%20in%20UP%20of%20which%20six%20were%20UC%2C%20two%20Muslim%2C%20two%20from%20Dalit%20communities%20and%20one%2C%20from%20an%20OBC%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%2013%20women%20MPs%20were%20elected%2C%20of%20whom%20five%20each%20were%20were%20Dalit%20and%20OBC%20communities%20while%20three%20were%20UC.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20of%20the%2011%20women%20MPs%20elected%2C%20five%20each%20were%20OBC%20and%20UC%2C%20while%20one%20was%20from%20a%20Dalit%20community.%20Seats%20are%20not%20reserved%20for%20the%20OBC%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20accurately%20identifying%20a%20married%20woman%20MP%E2%80%99s%20caste%20can%20be%20tricky%20in%20our%20patriarchal%20society%2C%20we%20have%20stuck%20to%20the%20surname%20and%20caste%20identity%20assumed%20by%20her%20after%20marriage%20rather%20than%20at%20birth.%20For%20instance%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%20MP%20Dimple%20Yadav%2C%20though%20born%20into%20a%20Kshatriya%20family%2C%20uses%20the%20OBC%20Yadav%20surname%20of%20her%20husband%2C%20Akhilesh.%20She%20is%20therefore%20counted%20as%20an%20OBC.%20It%20is%20easier%20to%20confirm%20the%20caste%20identity%20of%20MLAs%20in%20UP%20as%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20declare%20it%20in%20their%20bio-data%20in%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F02%2FDimple-Yadav.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dimple%20Yadav%20at%20a%20Samajwadi%20Party%20rally%20is%20Wazirganj%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20Credit%3A%20Ajoy%20Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221160%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-112153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22870%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDimple%20Yadav%20at%20a%20Samajwadi%20Party%20rally%20is%20Wazirganj%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20Photo%3A%20Ajoy%20Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Samajwadi%20Party%20came%20to%20power%20in%20UP%20in%202012%20with%20a%20comfortable%20majority.%20In%202017%20and%202022%2C%20the%20elections%20were%20won%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20with%20even%20greater%20seat%20tallies.%20A%20government-wise%20break-up%20shows%20that%20when%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20was%20in%20power%20from%20the%20time%20of%20his%20election%20in%202012%20to%20March%202017%2C%2013%20OBC%20women%2C%2013%20Dalit%20women%2C%2011%20UC%20women%20and%20three%20Muslim%20women%20were%20elected%20as%20MLAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20tenure%20of%20Chief%20Minister%20Adityanath%2C%20from%202017%20March%20to%202022%2C%2013%20OBC%20women%2C%2012%20Dalit%20women%2C%2020%20UC%20women%20and%201%20Muslim%20woman%20were%20elected%20as%20MLAs.%20During%20Adityanath%E2%80%99s%20second%20tenure%2C%20which%20is%20still%20on%2C%2013%20OBC%20women%2C%2021%20Dalit%20women%2C%2011%20UC%20women%20and%20three%20Muslim%20women%20were%20elected.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20accurate%20data%20for%20the%20present%20OBC%20and%20UC%20populations%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20caste%20census.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20according%20to%20the%201931%20caste-based%20survey%20and%20surveys%20published%20by%20various%20government%20commissions%20thereafter%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20Hindu%20OBCs%20itself%20in%20UP%20was%20upwards%20of%2040%25%20of%20the%20total%20population.%20The%202001%20social%20justice%20committee%20headed%20by%20Hukum%20Singh%20had%20calculated%20the%20total%20OBC%20population%20in%20UP%20to%20be%2054.05%25.%20The%20estimate%20of%20the%20OBC%20population%20is%20important%20to%20reflect%20the%20disproportionate%20representation%20enjoyed%20by%20UC%20candidates%20in%20power.%20Around%20one-fifth%20(19.5%25)%20of%20UP%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20Muslim%20while%20another%2021.5%20%25%20are%20SCs%2C%20according%20to%202011%20Census%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20caste%20figures%20of%20just%20the%20last%20three%20assembly%20elections%20show%20that%20Muslim%20women%20represented%20only%205%25%20of%20the%20women%20elected%20in%20the%20assembly%2C%20while%20OBC%20women%20represented%2029%25%20and%20UC%20women%2031%25%20of%20the%20total%20women%20legislators.%20The%20share%20of%20the%20SC%20women%20was%2034%25%2C%20but%20all%20of%20the%20seats%20they%20were%20elected%20from%20were%20constituencies%20reserved%20for%20the%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20UCs%2C%20most%20of%20the%20women%20MLAs%20in%202012%2C%202017%20and%202022%20belonged%20to%20the%20Thakur%20and%20Rajput%20communities%20(21)%20followed%20by%20Brahmins%20(16)%2C%20Baniya%20(3)%2C%20Bhumihar%20(1)%20and%20Kayastha%20(1).%20As%20many%20as%2012%20Thakur%20and%20Rajput%20women%20MLAs%20were%20elected%20in%20the%20period%202017-2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%2052-member%20Adityanath%20council%20of%20ministers%20at%20present%20has%20only%20four%20women%20ministers.%20While%20three%20%E2%80%93%20Baby%20Rani%20Maurya%2C%20Gulab%20Devi%20and%20Vijay%20Laxmi%20Gautam%20%E2%80%93%20are%20from%20Dalit%20communities%2C%20one%20(Rajni%20Tiwari)%20is%20a%20Brahmin.%20Maurya%20is%20the%20only%20woman%20cabinet%20minister%20in%20the%20present%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20if%20we%20compare%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20in%20the%20two%20governments%20run%20by%20Adityanath%20%E2%80%93%202017%20and%202022%20%E2%80%93%20we%20find%20that%20while%20UCs%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20disproportionate%20representation%2C%20the%20share%20of%20OBCs%20has%20improved%20in%20the%20second%20tenure%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20today%2C%20out%20of%2052%20ministers%20in%20UP%2C%20OBCs%20and%20UCs%20occupy%2021%20berths%20each%2C%20which%20is%2040.38%25%20each.%20Dalits%20hold%2017.3%25%20of%20the%20posts%2C%20with%20nine%20ministers.%20There%20is%20a%20lone%20Muslim%20minister.%20In%20September%202021%2C%20when%20the%20first%20Adityanath%20government%E2%80%99s%20council%20of%20ministers%20had%20reached%20its%20maximum%20allowed%20strength%20of%2060%2C%20it%20had%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20UCs.%20Out%20of%20the%2060%20ministers%2C%2027%20(45%25)%20were%20UC%2C%2023%20(38.3%25)%20were%20OBC%20and%20nine%20(15%25)%20were%20Dalits.%20Then%20too%2C%20there%20was%20just%20a%20single%20token%20Muslim%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20could%20explain%20the%20greater%20representation%20in%20power%20given%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20OBCs%20in%20the%20second%20Adityanath%20government%20to%20the%20shift%20in%20politics%20of%20its%20main%20rival%20in%20UP%2C%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%2C%20who%20has%20openly%20embraced%20social%20justice%20rhetoric%20and%20strategy%20of%20providing%20more%20space%20to%20OBC%20and%20Dalit%20faces%20and%20issues.%20The%202022%20election%2C%20which%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-strong-is-akhilesh-yadavs-new-electoral-formula%5C%22%3E%20Yadav%20lost%20despite%20putting%20up%20a%20brave%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20nominating%20a%20rainbow%20of%20OBC%20candidates%2C%20would%20be%20remembered%20for%20him%20promising%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20caste%20census%20and%20providing%20the%20%E2%80%98Bahujans%E2%80%99%20their%20%E2%80%9Crights%2C%20honour%20and%20representation%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20their%20share%20in%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20also%20taking%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Bahujan%20politics%20icon%20Kanshiram%E2%80%99s%20book%20and%20echoing%20the%20slogan%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJiski%20jitni%20sankhya%20bhari%2C%20uski%20utni%20hissedari%20%3C%2Fem%3E(those%20with%20the%20numbers%20have%20the%20stake)%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20wonders%20if%20the%20Congress%20is%20also%20willing%20to%20fully%20embrace%20social%20justice%20politics%20that%20it%20had%20shied%20away%20from%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20exclusion%20of%20a%20defined%20quota%20for%20OBC%20women%20in%20the%20women%20reservation%20and%20its%20indefinite%20implementation%20programme%20have%20provided%20a%20common%20ground%20for%20social%20justice%20politics%20for%20the%20Congress%20and%20its%20Mandal%20politics%20allies%20in%20UP%20and%20Bihar%2C%20which%20together%20have%20120%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20will%20they%20take%20the%20narrative%20beyond%20the%20walls%20of%20parliament%20and%20to%20the%20people%20as%20we%20head%20to%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%3F%20The%20caste%20census%20may%20be%20a%20long-time%20waiting%20but%20for%20now%2C%20can%20the%20ruling%20party%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Opposition%20parties%20tell%20us%20how%20many%20OBC%20and%20women%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20are%20there%20in%20the%20country%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695611844000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25084512%2F3438534368_7d25f489ec_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3