tps%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24183157%2Fcontent.jpeg%20728w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20Life%20in%20Poetry%20by%20Varavara%20Rao.%20Publisher%3A%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20India%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20essay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENecessity%20of%20Atheism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Percy%20Shelly%20identifies%20three%20indicators%20for%20the%20non-existence%20of%20God%20%E2%80%93%20lack%20of%20sensory%20input%2C%20presence%20of%20reason%20and%20an%20absence%20of%20testimony%20of%20God%E2%80%99s%20presence.%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20is%20similar%20to%20these%20three%20%E2%80%9Cexcitements%E2%80%9D%20as%20Shelly%20calls%20them%2C%20for%20rightly%20refuting%20the%20existence%20of%20order%20and%20equality%20in%20Indian%20society.%20The%2048%20poems%20trace%20the%20timeline%20of%20the%20historical%20inevitability%20that%20India%20is.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20book%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20defining%20moments%20captured%20through%20absolutely%20stunning%20language%20and%20pain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20we%20set%20on%20a%20path%20to%20decipher%20Rao%2C%20the%20poet%2C%20he%20reveals%20himself.%20His%20own%20analysis%20of%20poetry%20is%20like%20the%20spirit%20of%20a%20free%20bird%20and%20his%20language%20its%20wings.%20In%20a%20poem%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPoetry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Rao%20says%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPoetry%20is%20truth%20that%20need%20not%20be%20concealed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20who%20do%20not%20need%20government%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELife%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20need%20ambrosia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20keeping%20up%20his%20words%2C%20Rao%20has%20not%20hidden%20any%20truth%20which%20was%20worth%20the%20salt%20throughout%20his%20life%20as%20well%20as%20in%20this%20anthology%20of%20his%20poetry.%20The%20unwanted%20ambrosia%20of%20life%20is%20akin%20to%20Faiz%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esheereeni-e-farda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20his%20famous%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDua%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Faiz%20had%20written%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAaiye%20arz%20guzarein%2C%20k%20nigaar-e-hasti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZeher-e-imroz%20mein%20sheereeni-e-farda%20bhar%20de%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(Come%20let%20us%20pray%20that%20the%20creator%20may%20fill%20sweetness%20in%20tomorrow%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Etaking%20away%20the%20poison%20of%20today).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sweet%20nectar%20of%20tomorrow%20is%20thus%20a%20promise%20of%20hope%20for%20both%20the%20hopeful%20Faiz%20as%20well%20as%20for%20the%20not%20so%20hopeful%20Rao%20but%20it%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98poison%20of%20today%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20fills%20the%20lives%20of%20common%20people%2C%20that%20finds%20its%20way%20in%20their%20recitations.%20Both%20are%20thus%20peoples%E2%80%99%20poets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20young%20teenager%20I%20still%20remember%20the%20day%20when%20in%20September%2C%201987%2C%20Roop%20Kanwar%2C%20a%20married%20Rajasthani%20girl%20was%20burnt%20on%20the%20pyre%20of%20her%20husband%20as%20part%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESati%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20tradition.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20haunting%20poems%20of%20this%20anthology%20is%20a%20poem%20describing%20Roop%E2%80%99s%20plight.%20It%E2%80%99s%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChunri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20is%20a%20revelation%20of%20this%20mediaeval%20tradition%20of%20gruesome%20patriarchy.%20The%20last%20verses%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChunri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20heartbreaking%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20dragged%20her%20on%20his%20pyre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20he%20would%20drag%20her%20on%20his%20bed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20same%20authority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20performed%20Sati%20as%20freely%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20she%20lived%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQualifying%20something%20as%20brutal%20and%20ugly%20as%20misogyny%20through%20poetry%20is%20what%20makes%20Rao%20a%20poet%20worth%20reading.%20He%20holds%20our%20hand%20and%20walks%20us%20into%20a%20cold%20dark%20space%20where%20life%20is%20not%20what%20we%20are%20made%20to%20believe.%20There%20is%20rather%20an%20infinite%20absence%20of%20life%20all%20around%20in%20that%20real%20space.%20His%20poem%20reminds%20me%20of%20Sylvia%20Plath%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELady%20Lazarus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20it%2C%20she%20says%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20done%20it%20again.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20year%20in%20every%20ten%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20manage%20it%E2%80%94%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sort%20of%20walking%20miracle%2C%20my%20skin%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBright%20as%20a%20Nazi%20lampshade%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20right%20foot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20paperweight%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20face%20a%20featureless%2C%20fine%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJew%20linen%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20%E2%80%98Nazi%20lampshade%E2%80%99%20of%20Plath%E2%80%99s%2C%20to%20me%2C%20finds%20reflection%20in%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20Sati.%20Both%20have%20a%20poignant%20theatrical%20value%20in%20their%20verses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20book%2C%20Meena%20Kandasamy%20says%20that%20Rao%20is%20perhaps%20the%20longest%20jailed%20poet%20in%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20history.%20Like%20the%20Spanish%20poet%20Federico%20Garcia%20Lorca%2C%20imprisonment%20probably%20sets%20the%20poet%20free.%20Lorca%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Prisoner%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Etells%20us%20about%20that%20girl%20lost%20in%20the%20dark%20night%20who%20reflected%20daylight%20with%20the%20splendor%20of%20her%20unclouded%20forehead.%20Rao%20uses%20less%20metaphors%20and%20more%20realism%20when%20he%20writes%20about%20the%20prison.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fvaravara-rao-young-poet-public-statement%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Attack%20on%20Varavara%20Rao%20Is%20an%20Attack%20on%20All%20of%20Us%E2%80%99%3A%20Young%20Poets%20Urge%20Release%20of%20Activist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESab%20Theekh%20Hai%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewritten%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eduring%20his%20second%20jail%20sentence%20between%20May%201974%20and%20April%201975%2C%20Rao%20describes%20how%20the%20tired%20night%20guards%20screamed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esab%20theekh%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(all%20is%20well)%20every%20hour.%20The%20metaphorical%20beauty%20of%20this%20poem%20is%20difficult%20to%20describe%20in%20words.%20Rao%20writes%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20moon%20gets%20caught%20in%20the%20barbed%20wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20prison%20walls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20we%2C%20after%20singing%20and%20talking%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELose%20ourselves%20in%20the%20dreams%20of%20revolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20difficulty%20of%20these%20verses%20is%20not%20the%20presence%20of%20metaphors%20but%20the%20inability%20to%20distinguish%20between%20metaphors%20and%20corporeality.%20They%20are%20blended%20like%20the%20dusk%20and%20the%20night.%20The%20moon%2C%20the%20barbed%20wire%2C%20prison%20walls%2C%20singing%20or%20maybe%20the%20dream%20of%20revolution%20%E2%80%93%20all%20fall%20in%20the%20preview%20of%20our%20own%20perception%20and%20conscious%20volition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20can%20we%20infer%20in%20a%20society%20which%20harbours%20death%20and%20life%2C%20joy%20and%20sadness%2C%20poverty%20and%20richness%2C%20hunger%20and%20satiety%20with%20equal%20passive%20perception%3F%20What%20happens%20when%20nations%20make%20sad%20metaphors%20an%20actuality%3F%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20it%20ironic%20that%20such%20a%20poem%20is%20published%20in%20times%20when%20the%20highest%20executive%20of%20the%20nation%20made%20a%20similar%20comment%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESab%20changa%20si%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(all%20is%20well).%20Remember%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20poets%20have%20a%20prophetic%20appeal!%20They%20know%20the%20future%20better%20than%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFriedrich%20Nietzsche%20had%20once%20written%20that%20if%20you%20kill%20a%20cockroach%2C%20you%20are%20a%20hero%2C%20if%20you%20kill%20a%20butterfly%2C%20you%20are%20evil.%20Morals%20have%20aesthetic%20criteria.%20The%20aesthetics%20of%20morality%20is%20thus%20a%20slippery%20slope.%20The%20reality%20of%20this%20aesthetic%20criteria%20is%20best%20demonstrated%20by%20Rao%20in%20a%20poem%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ED%C3%A9j%C3%A0%20vu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELucky%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20are%20born%20rich.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20you%20say%20in%20your%20lingo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Born%20with%20a%20silver%20spoon%20in%20the%20mouth%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYour%20agitation%20sounds%20creative%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20agony%20appears%20violent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20can%20deflate%20tyres%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20artistic%20elan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20indulgent%20police%20look%20on%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20jaws%20nestling%20on%20rifle%20butts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20are%20told%20that%20this%20poem%20was%20written%20by%20Rao%20following%20an%20agitation%20of%20the%20upper%20caste%2C%20upper%20class%20youths%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20in%201986%20against%20a%20state%20level%20commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20for%20increasing%20reservations.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20apt%20representation%20of%20what%20Nietzsche%20had%20inferred%20a%20few%20decades%20back.%20In%20%E2%80%98merit%20hungry%20nations%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20is%20only%20with%20those%20who%20hardly%20need%20protests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20speak%20of%20poetry%2C%20we%20speak%20of%20chaos.%20Poetry%20which%20invokes%20chaos%20is%20poetry%20which%20gives%20hope.%20Hope%20lies%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20chaos.%20In%20a%20nation%20which%20is%20reeling%20under%20majoritarianism%2C%20communalism%20and%20casteism%2C%20what%20hope%20can%20we%20infer%20from%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20poetry%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pretence%20of%20hope%20has%20been%20endured%20since%20eternity%20and%20poets%20are%20the%20harbingers%20of%20this%20pretence.%20Some%20like%20Rao%20have%20been%20bestowed%20the%20job%20of%20making%20the%20pretence%20real.%20They%20work%20to%20make%20us%20believe%20in%20hope.%20Despite%20incarceration%2C%20despite%20state%20suppression%20to%20curb%20his%20spirits%2C%20and%20despite%20all%20methods%20to%20drown%20his%20voice%2C%20Rao%20roars%20with%20his%20poetry%20like%20a%20waterfall.%20His%20infectious%20courage%20makes%20those%20in%20power%20nervous%20as%20armed%20with%20such%20poignant%20beautiful%20poetry%2C%20Rao%20is%20a%20force%20to%20reckon%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dream%20Pigeons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20he%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPigeons%20released%20by%20heart%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAlight%20on%20the%20eyelids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20know%20I%20am%20scared%20to%20open%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20eyes%20and%20break%20the%20wings%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20so%2C%20I%20pretend%2C%20with%20my%20eyes%20closed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20know%20very%20well%20that%20my%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDreams%20are%20not%20my%20creations%20alone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20that%20imagination%20is%20not%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnyone%E2%80%99s%20secret.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMay%20his%20dream%20come%20true%20and%20may%20his%20imagination%20be%20on%20fire%2C%20always.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShah%20Alam%20Khan%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Orthopaedics%2C%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%2C%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695563136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F26100034%2FVaravara-Rao-flowers-collage.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Life%20in%20Poetry%20is%20an%20anthology%20of%2048%20poems%20written%20by%20Telugu%20poet-activist%20Varavara%20Rao%2C%20written%20over%20a%20period%20of%2050%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Woman%20Who%20Built%20an%20Oasis%20in%20the%20New%20Mexico%20Desert%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184618%2FIMG_0276.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDark%20clouds%20hung%20low%20over%20the%20high%20desert%20country.%20Shining%20through%20the%20clouds%2C%20bursts%20of%20golden%20orange%20cast%20a%20glow%20on%20a%20roadside%20sign%20that%20read%2C%20%E2%80%98Pigs.%E2%80%99%20I%20was%20in%20northern%20New%20Mexico%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EBreaking%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EBad%3C%2Fem%3E%20land.%20This%20road%20sign%20was%20my%20left%20turn%2C%20leading%20me%20straight%20into%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20Owl%20Peaks%20hills.%20It%20was%20here%20that%20I%20would%20rendezvous%20with%20our%20desert%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELa%20Patrona%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EC.C.%20Culver%2C%20a%20patron%20of%20agriculture%2C%20ecology%2C%20and%20sustainability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20over%20three%20and%20a%20half%20decades%2C%20Culver%20has%20been%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20conservation%20and%20re-wilding%20of%20the%20quaint%20rural%20high%20desert%20village%20of%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%20Her%20tireless%20efforts%20in%20regenerative%20farming%20and%20community%20building%20had%20transformed%20this%20little%20oasis%20into%20a%20thriving%20example%20of%20eco-friendly%20living%2C%20not%20only%20for%20humans%20but%20also%20the%20beavers%20and%20peacocks%2C%20and%20even%20unfriendly%20weeds.%20Keep%20in%20mind%20the%20village%2C%20which%20this%20area%20is%20a%20part%20of%2C%20besides%20being%20one%20of%20the%20poorest%20regions%20of%20the%20US%2C%20it%20is%20also%20plagued%20by%20by%20an%20undercurrent%20of%20racial%20tension%20between%20the%20native%20or%20indigenous%20people%2C%20Hispanics%20and%20Anglo.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENevertheless%20her%20experiments%20with%20agriculture%20have%20brought%20back%20many%20heirloom%20varieties%20like%20blue%20corn%2C%20sonora%20wheat%2C%20many%20types%20of%20chillies%20and%20even%20the%20amaranth%20millets%20to%20New%20Mexico.%20She%20has%20helped%20shape%20the%20%E2%80%98beyond%20organic%E2%80%99%20movement%2C%20not%20only%20in%20New%20Mexico%20and%20the%20American%20Southwest%20but%20also%20internationally.%20She%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20key%20international%20movements%20like%20Slow%20Food%2C%20Slow%20Money%2C%20the%20Quivira%20Coalition%2C%20the%20Southwest%20Grain%20Collaborative%2C%20Qachuu%20Aloom%20(Guatemala)%2C%20ancient%20grain%20revival%20measures%20and%20more.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184745%2FIMG_0292-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184745%2FIMG_0292-1.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184745%2FIMG_0292-1-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184745%2FIMG_0292-1-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674611%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECulver%E2%80%99s%20farm%20in%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%20Photo%3A%20Indra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20day%20with%20%E2%80%98CC%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%207%20am%20on%20a%20Saturday%20when%20I%20meet%20up%20with%20CC.%20She%20is%20in%20wet%20boots%20and%20has%20her%20task%20list%20in%20hand.%20I%20sat%20in%20her%20car%20along%20with%20Lucy%2C%20her%20dog%20and%20two%20cats%2C%20Charles%20and%20Puss.%20Before%20feeding%20her%20horse%2C%20she%20gave%20me%20a%20mini%20tour%20of%20her%20thorny%20paradise.%20Most%20of%20her%20farm%20is%20not%20cultivable%20due%20to%20scarcity%20of%20water%2C%20sandy%20soil%20or%20hilly%20terrain.%20In%20other%20parts%2C%20she%20let%20junipers%2C%20cedars%2C%20cactuses%20and%20even%20the%20desert%20rat%20run%20wild.%C2%A0%20Swerving%20on%20the%20sand%20trail%2C%20we%20reach%20the%20horses.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20hungry%20horses%20ran%20towards%20us%2C%20we%20quickly%20give%20them%20a%20corn%20and%20hay%20breakfast.%20Next%2C%20we%20have%20to%20activate%20the%20gravity%20fed%20water%20sprinklers.%20Here%20is%20where%20I%20notice%20adolescent%20wheat%20plants%20shining%20in%20the%20morning%20sun.%20They%20are%20unlike%20the%20%E2%80%9CGreen%20Revolution%E2%80%9D%20wheat%20varieties%2C%20so%20I%20ask%20about%20them.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20Spanish%20Sonora%20wheat.%20They%20bought%20this%20over%20in%20the%2015%20century.%20Over%20time%20newer%20varieties%20came%2C%20and%20this%20seed%20was%20lost.%20Today%20we%20have%20revived%20this%20variety%20and%20also%20started%20giving%20it%20to%20other%20farmers%20to%20grow%20and%20to%20community%20members%20and%20restaurants%20as%20flour.%20This%20seed%20is%20part%20of%20New%20Mexico%20heritage%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%20in%20the%20US%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20craze%20for%20Sonora%20seeds%20and%20flour%20in%20the%20regenerative%20agriculture%20world.%20Before%20the%20Spanish%2C%20the%20Americas%20did%20not%20have%20wheat.%20So%20Sonora%20wheat%20plays%20an%20important%20historical-cultural%20role.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20farm%20and%20foundation%2C%20Owl%20Peak%2C%20is%20currently%20researching%20this%20hardy%20wheat%20for%20its%20cover%20crop%2C%20harvesting%20potential%20and%20its%20possibilities%20in%20building%20soil%20in%20the%20high%20desert.%20Conversation%20with%20bakers%20and%20restaurants%20in%20Santa%20Fe%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20Sonora%20wheat%20is%20growing%20to%20be%20the%20customer%E2%80%99s%20choice%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185046%2FIMG_0318-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674612%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECulver%E2%80%99s%20farm%20in%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Indra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENext%20it%20is%20time%20to%20feed%20the%20chickens%20and%20see%20the%20garlic%20fields.%20So%20we%20drive%20on%20the%20sandy%20trail%20towards%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Earroyo%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20then%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20chickens%20house.%20As%20we%20enter%20the%20farm%2C%20CC%20takes%20me%20down%20memory%20lane.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20the%20first%20farm%20I%20starting%20to%20work%20on%2C%20it%20was%20nothing%20like%20this%20when%20we%20started.%20The%20soil%20was%20very%20bad%2C%20the%20house%2C%20toolshed%20and%20green%20house%20weren%E2%80%99t%20there.%20We%20made%20all%20of%20it%2C%20and%20simultaneously%20started%20the%20experiments%20with%20soil%20building%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20different%20sections%20of%20the%20farm.%20From%20permaculture%20to%20Hugelkultur%20pits%2C%20she%20has%20tried%20to%20employ%20the%20best%20ideas%20to%20build%20soils%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%2C%20eco-agri%20researchers%20and%20experts%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%20have%20come%20here%20and%20tried%20to%20tell%20us%20what%20to%20do.%20We%20even%20tried%20to%20implement%20their%20designs%20and%20techniques.%20Most%20of%20them%20simply%20failed%20because%20the%20desert%20is%20a%20hard%20place%20and%20it%20has%20its%20own%20way.%20Over%20time%20I%20came%20to%20understand%20and%20live%20with%20this.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20had%20extreme%20drought%20for%20many%20years%2C%20and%20then%20randomly%20we%20received%20an%20above%20average%20snowfall%2C%20or%20a%20regular%20monsoon%20season%2C%20giving%20us%20just%20enough%20to%20survive.%20I%20try%20to%20observe%2C%20adapt%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20quickly%20disappears%20in%20the%20chicken%20coop%20and%20the%20little%20birds%20are%20upon%20her.%20A%20mixed%20corn%20meal%2C%20two%20packets%20of%20salad%20leaves%20and%20some%20fresh%20water%20is%20served.%20In%20return%20we%20collect%20some%20of%20multicoloured%20eggs%20and%20walked%20to%20the%20greenhouse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20the%20fig%20tree%20and%20Japanese%20mustard%20samplings%20we%20talked%20about%20her%20eco-agri%20pedagogue.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20is%20this%20is%20for%20the%20community.%20Overtime%20we%20have%20empowered%20many%20of%20the%20community%20members%20to%20join%20us%20here%20for%20residencies%20in%20eco-agriculture%2C%20food%2C%20environment%20and%20art.%20We%20had%20an%20indigenous%20chilly%20project%2C%20amaranth%20revival%20project%2C%20blue%20corn%20project%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20but%20many%20artists%20and%20chefs%20have%20also%20worked%20on%20food%20here.%20Our%20farm%20has%20hosted%20%E2%80%98donation%20only%E2%80%99%20meals%2C%20to%20bring%20the%20community%20together.%20A%20platform%20where%20people%20can%20meet%20and%20grow%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20while%20plucking%20some%20green%20herbs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20like%20to%20support%20people%2C%20be%20themselves%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20384px)%2085vw%2C%20384px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943.jpeg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943-225x300.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24185139%2FIMG_0328-e1695561729943-768x1024.jpeg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674613%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECulver%E2%80%99s%20farm%20in%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Indra%20Shekhar%20Singh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20about%20blue%20corn%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20getting%20to%20that.%E2%80%9D%20Off%20we%20went%20to%20Dora%E2%80%99s%20Farm.%20There%20is%20no%20Dora%20in%20the%20picture%20anymore%2C%20but%20CC%E2%80%99s%20third%20farm%20is%20named%20after%20its%20original%20owner.%20She%20and%20her%20team%20manage%2012%20acres%20%E2%80%93%20a%20size%20which%20is%20considered%20a%20very%20small%20farm%20in%20America.%20At%20Dora%E2%80%99s%20Farm%2C%20she%20introduces%20me%20to%20a%20Mexican%20man%2C%20Roberto%2C%20the%20farm%20manager.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20worked%20together%20as%20a%20team%20for%20many%20years%20now%2C%20trying%20to%20rejuvenate%20the%20place.%20I%20have%20removed%20the%20convention%20work-power%20hierarchy%20from%20our%20organisation.%20We%20are%20more%20like%20a%20family%2C%20working%20for%20this%20village.%20And%20I%20offer%20my%20family%20members%20here%20the%20same%20courtesy%20and%20respect%20as%20they%20offer%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20getting%20curious%20about%20the%20blue%20corn%2C%20but%20CC%20goes%20marching%20onto%20the%20deep%20brown%20soil%20field%2C%20and%20calls%20me%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20young%20corn%20plants.%20The%20entire%20field%20is%20sown%20with%20blue%20corn.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20the%20arroyo%20has%20overflowed%2C%20flooding%20some%20part%20of%20our%20fields%2C%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20plant%20corn%20there.%20But%20we%20did%20use%20the%20fields%20this%20time%20for%20hay%2C%20beans%20and%20chilly.%20As%20we%20are%20in%20the%20International%20Year%20of%20Millets%2C%20I%20even%20am%20trying%20to%20grow%20some%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eragi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eamaranth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Emillets%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20tells%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20already%20beyond%20lunch%20time%2C%20she%20invites%20us%20to%20the%20Sala%2C%20a%20local%20village%20cafe%20run%20by%20the%20organisation.%20Here%20Linda%20greets%20us.%20She%20explained%20%E2%80%98donation%20only%E2%80%99%20model%2C%20for%20where%20you%20only%20give%20what%20you%20can%20give%20for%20the%20food.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20way%20we%20ensure%20that%20no%20one%20in%20our%20community%20goes%20hungry.%20All%20kinds%20of%20people%20come%20here%2C%20from%20addicts%20to%20cattle%20ranchers%20and%20an%20occasion%20a%20tourist%20or%20two%2C%20we%20offer%20nutritious%20and%20healthy%20food%2C%20till%20mid%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20CC%20remarks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20pick%20up%20a%20bowl%20of%20red%20chilli%20and%20sit.%20I%20am%20moved%20with%20her%20world.%20Why%20would%20she%20choose%20to%20do%20this%3F%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20it%20because%20I%20can.%20In%20my%20life%2C%20I%20am%20free%20and%20now%20want%20to%20help%20others%20around%20me.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20humans%2C%20there%20are%20beings%20I%20love%20more%20than%20humans%20too.%20Beavers%2C%20butterflies%2C%20ants%20and%20even%20the%20weeds%20in%20our%20fields%2C%20all%20need%20care%20and%20love.%20And%20I%20am%20only%20doing%20a%20small%20part%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20tells%20me%20and%20then%20points%20to%20a%20beautiful%20micaceous%20clay%20pot%2C%20next%20to%20the%20photo%20of%20her%20grand%20daughter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20legendary%20micaceous%20clay%20potter%20Felipe%20Ortega%20who%20drew%20me%20to%20this%20village.%20It%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20few%20years%20since%20he%20has%20passed%2C%20but%20somehow%20this%20place%20feels%20like%20home.%20And%20this%20is%20a%20home%20I%20created%20for%20myself%2C%20by%20myself.%20I%20find%20peace%20and%20solitude%20here%2C%20and%20hence%20I%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20almost%20evening%20now%2C%20and%20I%20am%20still%20in%20admiration%20of%20this%20woman%E2%80%99s%20journey.%20She%20was%20born%20in%20the%20American%20South%2C%20worked%20on%20boats%20in%20California%20and%20sailed%20on%20the%20high%20seas%20and%20finally%20settled%20in%20the%20desert.%20I%20left%20with%20a%20hopeful%20feeling%20because%20her%20farm%20and%20organisation%20were%20regenerative%20in%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20has%20nurtured%20many%20seeds%20and%20humans%20to%20reach%20their%20fullest%20potential%2C%20hence%20to%20all%20she%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELa%20Patrona.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20this%20dog-eat-dog%20world%2C%C2%A0%20empowering%20others%20to%20be%20of%20service%20to%20the%20earth%20is%20no%20little%20task.%20CC%20does%20it%20silently%20everyday.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Shekhar%20Singh%20is%20an%20independent%20agri-policy%20analyst%20and%20writer.%20He%20was%20the%20former%20director%2C%20policy%20and%20outreach%2C%20at%20NSAI.%20He%20also%20hosts%20The%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20talk%20show%2C%20Krishi%20ki%20baat%2FFarm%20Talks.%20He%20tweets%20%40indrassingh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695561775000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24184618%2FIMG_0276.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fla-patrona-agriculture-new-mexico-blue-corn%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20over%20three%20and%20a%20half%20decades%2C%20C.C.%20Culver%20has%20been%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20conservation%20and%20re-wilding%20of%20the%20quaint%20rural%20high%20desert%20village%20of%20La%20Madera%2C%20New%20Mexico.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fla-patrona-agriculture-new-mexico-blue-corn%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2